directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a large cookie sheet. Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition. Beat until stiff and glossy. Beat egg yolks and vanilla until thick and lemon colored. Add to egg whites and fold in gently but quickly. Fold in flour. Press through a pastry tube or cookie press, with large plain tip, into strips 2 1/2 inches long onto prepared cookie sheet. (If you don't have a pastry tube or cookie press, shape rounded teaspoonfuls of batter into strips.) Bake 8-10 minutes or until set and very lightly browned on the bottom. remove from sheets and cool on racks. Store in tightly closed tin box.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix thoroughly and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan or microwave.
In mixing bowl, add margarine and brown sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Boil tomatoes until soft; strain through a sieve.
Add vinegar, sugar, cayenne pepper, black pepper, cloves, mustard and salt.
Boil down until it is 1/4 of its bulk and add cinnamon. Bottle, seal and process.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: health food fudge
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together over medium heat for one minute.
Add cereal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir fast.
Drop on waxed paper to harden.

title: orange julius
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until well mixed.
Add sugar and blend again.
Add ice cubes, three at a time, and blend on high until completely crushed.
Pour into cups and serve immediately.
Makes 6 cups.

title: perfect sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugar and powdered sugar together; add vanilla, baking soda, cream of tartar, eggs and salt.
Mix well. Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Chill for 4 hours.
Shape into balls, roll in sugar, then flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes or until light brown on bottom.

title: broccoli for brunch(microwave)
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave as directed on package or on High setting (for fresh)
until tender.
Add margarine, salt and orange juice and heat in microwave until margarine is melted.
Top with toasted slivered almonds.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In small bowl, beat together egg white and water.
Stir in pecans, stirring until all surfaces are moistened.
Mix together sugar and remaining ingredients, sprinkle over pecans and mix well to coat all sides.
Spread on lightly greased or foil-lined cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir about halfway through baking time to assure crispness and even drying.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Remove from heat; mix in the chips. Stir and melt.
Add the oatmeal and mix well.
Drop dough from spoon onto a waxed paper lined tray.
When cooled they are ready to enjoy.

title: dreamy fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Beat in marshmallow cream.
Fold in whipped topping. Serve with fruit.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: about 4 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole bowl.
Top with 1 roll of Hi Ho or Ritz cracker crumbs (35 crackers), 1/2 cup slivered almonds and 1/2 cup margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandmother's pineapple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and pale yellow.
Beat or fold in Mascarpone until thoroughly incorporated. Mixture should be completely smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into Mascarpone mixture.

Combine Espresso and brandy. Dip ladyfingers very quickly into coffee-brandy mixture, one at a time, and line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch rectangular dish. Spread half of the Mascarpone mixture over the ladyfingers and sprinkle with powdered cocoa.
Dip more ladyfingers into the Espresso-brandy and make another layer.
Cover with Mascarpone and sprinkle with cocoa.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, peel some chocolate into curls with a carrot peeler and sprinkle over the cake.

title: good meatballs
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Shape into medium-size meatballs.
Fry gently in oil, until slightly browned, or place on foil-covered cookie sheet for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Gently place in your own hot spaghetti sauce and cook on medium-low heat for 1 hour.

title: stay soft chocolate frosting
directions: Blend together cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter.
Stir gently, until cool and thick enough to spread.
This will frost 2 layers.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse. Place in a 2 1/2-quart salad bowl.
Add turkey, celery, onion and green pepper.
Toss to mix.
Combine dressing mix, sour cream, salad dressing and garlic salt.
Add to pasta mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Garnish with pepper ring and tomato slice, if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma mary's barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana fudge walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of an 8-inch square pan.
Melt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat stirring constantly the butter and chocolate chips.
Beat in thoroughly with spoon the rest of the ingredients. Spread batter evenly in
pan. Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set. Cool completely. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 4 min. of cooking time. Drain.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple.
Save about 2 tablespoons for dissolving gelatin.
Add nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Dissolve gelatin in pineapple juice.
Mix into salad.
Chill.

title: amaretto apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into a dry measuring cup.
Level with a knife.
Combine flour and sugar in bowl; cut in butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is crumbly.
Add almonds; toss well.
Combine apple and Amaretto in a bowl.
TOSS WELL.
Spoon apple mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: last-time-ever-i-saw-my-waist cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake mix using package directions for a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix cream cheese and whipped topping in a bowl. Spread over cooled cake.
Combine pudding mix and milk in a bowl.
Mix well. Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining 8 ounces whipped topping. Chill until serving time.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: memoo's tomato aspic
directions: Boil water.
Add to gelatin.
Stir until dissolves.
Add tomato sauce and vinegar; stir.
Chill slightly.
Add vegetables. Pour into individual serving dishes or 8 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Serve over bed of lettuce.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add sauce.
Cook noodles.
Blend eggs, Ricotta and 1 cup Parmesan.
Alternate layers, starting with meat sauce, noodles, Ricotta mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat. End with noodle layer.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 bread loaf pans.

title: pizza margherita
directions: Brush the dough or crust with a little olive oil to the edge. Spread tomato sauce over the dough to within 1/2-inch of the edge. Distribute Mozzarella slices over the tomato sauce and season with pepper.
Arrange basil leaves over the Mozzarella, reserving a few garnish if you wish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Drizzle with the remaining olive oil.
Carefully slide the pizza in the oven and bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until the bottom if crisp and browned and the top is bubbling.
Garnish with the reserved basil leaves, if desired.
Yield:
one 12-inch pizza.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, oil and egg together.
When well blended, add sifted flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Blend well, then add oatmeal, nuts, coconut and Rice Krispies, stirring just enough with a wooden spoon to mix.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Sift 1/2 dry ingredients into sugar-oil mixture. Blend well.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well.
Add nuts last.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
After, cool at least 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.
Can sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown the meat with the onion.
Mix together all ingredients except the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add noodles.
Mix 3/4 into the casserole and spread the rest evenly over the top. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken picante
directions: In large bowl, combine taco sauce, mustard and lime juice; mix well.
Add chicken, turning to coat; marinate for 30 minutes.
In large heavy skillet, melt butter until foamy.
Remove chicken from marinade; fry until browned on all sides, turning frequently.
Add remaining marinade; cook about 5 minutes longer, until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove chicken, boil marinade 1 minute and spoon over chicken.
Place 1 tablespoon sour cream on top of each piece; top with lime segment.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, melt the butter.
Stir in flour; heat and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add potatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: chunky chocolate chip brownie-type cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla together.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Gradually add in flour on medium speed of mixer.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 25 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix first seven ingredients.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into 1 pound coffee cans, filling cans about halfway.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle 2
directions: Vegetables:
butter beans, peas, squash, corn, any vegetable you would freeze.

title: corn bread(egg-free and milk-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients and beat well. Bake in a greased and floured 8-inch cake pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Beat egg in medium bowl.
Mix in bread crumbs, chili sauce, salt, onion, garlic powder, ground beef and celery.
Shape into 30 small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Melt Crisco in large skillet on medium heat.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides. Continue cooking until done, about 12 minutes including browning. Warm barbecue sauce while meatballs cook.
Serve meatballs on wooden picks to be dipped in warm sauce.

title: cake, jello and pudding dessert
directions: Slice cake and place on bottom of 9x13 pan.
Prepare Jello and pour over cake.
Chill until set.
Slice bananas over cake and Jello.
Prepare pudding.
Spread over bananas.
Let set 5-10 minutes in refrigerator. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Refrigerate.

title: potato soup hash
directions: In a large soup pot, cook roast.
When done, remove roast and add diced onion, celery and cubed potatoes to broth.
When potatoes are almost done, add soups.
In the meantime, shred up roast and add to pot.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well (until all cream cheese is worked in).
Place on plate, form ball and refrigerate.
Can be rolled in chopped nuts or parsley before serving.

title: four minute icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat to stiff peaks, 4 minutes over boiling water.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top if you like.

title: emily's mussels in wine
directions: With a stiff brush, scrub mussels with running cold water to remove sand or beards.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, wine and basil.
Then heat to a boil over high heat.
Add mussels and once again heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until mussels open, about 5 minutes.
Serve with bread and salad.

title: mud pie cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa powder, salt and baking soda.
Add water, oil, egg, vinegar and vanilla and pour in a large 8 x 14-inch cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Blend well, then add chocolate chips.
Set aside. Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Then add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Put chocolate mixture in greased pan and then spread cheese mix evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well. Pour into greased (only) muffin pan. Mix 1 tsp. of cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle on top of muffins.
Bake at 350° for 15 min.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a large skillet or muffin pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch
and cold water; add boiling water and stir until thick
and clear.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar, then beat
until stiff, but not dry.
Add salt, vanilla and cornstarch mixture	and beat well.	Spread on pie and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake pie crusts for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients. Mix into the pumpkin.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix with spoon.
Pour 1/2 into each crust.
Be careful not to overfill or to get mix on edges of pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Check after 30 minutes.
Can freeze 1/2 of mixture and bake it later.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients and then add milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a prepared graham cracker crust and freeze overnight.
Just before serving, remove from the freezer and let stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, milk and pepper in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix well.
Stir in beans and half of the onions.
Bake 10 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle casserole with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until hot and onions are golden.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Pour spaghetti sauce into hamburger.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix cream potatoes as directed on box and layer on top of hamburger mixture.
You can sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Work first 6 ingredients together real good.
Make a hole in flour, then add buttermilk (enough to take up all the flour, but enough to knead a little bit).
Then put out on pastry sheet. Knead just enough to flatten with hand.
Don't overwork.
Then cut and bake at 425° until light brown.
When taken from oven, put butter on top and cover for 6 minutes.
Serve.

title: cream cheese party mints
directions: Mix ingredients well by hand.
Add desired color.
Take a small piece, dip in sugar and press in plastic mold.
Drop out of mold onto waxed paper.
Let dry for a while before putting in covered container.
Can be frozen in airtight container for later use.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix bouillon cubes, water, onion, celery and potatoes together.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1 cup water.
Add Velveeta cheese and cook slowly until all cheese is melted.
Sprinkle in bacon crumbs.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, blend in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix real good, add dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon full on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Layer the bottom of the unbaked pie shells with the nuts. Then mix all the ingredients and pour onto the pecans in the pie shell.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
The edges will become firm and the middle will look soft, but it will thicken when it cools.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Use a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Quarter cabbage and cut off core.
Boil over medium heat in salted water until tender.
(Do not overcook.)
Pour into colander and cool.
Mix all dry ingredients. Place cabbage leaves on chopping board and cut out middle stem. Make layers of cabbage leaves, dry mixture and drizzle 1/4 cup olive oil.
Continue making layers, ending with dry ingredients and olive oil.
(Make 4 layers.)
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made the day before, placed in refrigerator and when cold, cut into squares.
When ready to serve, warm in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be eaten cold.

title: spanish rice with turkey
directions: Cook turkey, onions and pepper until done, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.
Counts as 3 proteins, vegetable and 1 bread.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after each egg.
Add dry ingredients along with milk and flavoring.
Cook in tube pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus in casserole.
Spread mushrooms on top of asparagus.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: becky's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil to small ball stage in 3-quart pan.
Beat with mixer until mixture cools a little.
(Starts to cool to side of pan somewhat.)
Add nuts (optional).
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan if recipe is doubled.

title: holiday eggnog punch
directions: Mix ice cream, eggnog and Seven-Up in large container or punch bowl.
Ice cream need not be completely blended in.
Serve with a candy cane for stirring.
Yields 24 servings.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place Canadian bacon in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place a chicken breast on each piece of Canadian bacon and top with a 1/2 slice of bacon.
Bake for 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with mushroom soup and sour cream mixed together.
Bake for 30 minutes more at 350°.
Serve with chopped green onions.

title: frittata
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan or Dutch oven.
Add vegetables, mushrooms, garlic and bell pepper.
Stir, cover and cook for 3 minutes.
In a bowl, combine meat, eggs, salt and pepper and cheese.
Stir into the vegetable mixture.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or serve with warm coffee cream.

title: vegetarian vegetable soup(stone soup)
directions: Wash and cut vegetables.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add onions and celery and simmer until soft.
Remove from heat; slowly add 3 quarts of boiling water.
Add seasonings and vegetables, macaroni and rice; boil until vegetables are tender (about 20 or 30 minutes).
Add tomato soup; heat.
Add more water, if needed.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients with beef and put in crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a prepared unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Have oven preheated to 450°.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and bake another 25 minutes or until custard is mostly set and crust is browned.

title: pasta and cauliflower soup
directions: Break the cauliflower into its flowerets, cutting the bigger ones in halves or quarters so that all the pieces are about 1/2-inch in size.
Put the oil in a soup pot along with the garlic, salt, pepper and the cut-up cauliflower.
Stirring gently, cook over medium heat until the vegetable bits are well oiled and flavored.
Add the tomato paste, hot water, the potato slices and 2 teaspoons salt and bring to a boil.
Break the pasta into 1 or 2-inch lengths as you put it in the pot.
Continue boiling until the pasta is well cooked, has absorbed some of the water and the cauliflower, garlic and tomato have lent their flavors to the pasta.
Before serving discard the garlic clove.
Serve with a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.

title: asparagus ham dinner
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile in a non-stick skillet; saute asparagus, yellow and red bell peppers in oil until tender. Add tomatoes and ham; heat thoroughly. Drain pasta, add to vegetable mixture. Stir in seasonings. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: ground beef-noodle casserole
directions: In one bowl, mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream. Cook noodles.
Alternate noodles and cheese mixture in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until mixture thickens (cook just a little more than soft ball stage on a candy thermometer).
Beat eggs without separating and slowly add eggs to hot syrup, beating constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 4 cup glass measuring cup, combine sugar and corn syrup. Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; cook 1 minute.
Quickly fold in baking soda. Spread on greased cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: citrus sunshine punch
directions: Dissolve orange juice, lemonade, limeade and water together; add ginger ale and serve.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine chicken, water, vinegar, bay leaf, garlic, pepper and soy sauce in a medium to large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover and lower heat.
Cook until chicken is done and a small amount of broth is left.
Add the oil and brown the contents of the pan, if desired.
(Cooking time is 45 to 60 minutes average.)
Serve over rice.

title: easy cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in a large bowl (large enough to hold all ingredients).
Mix dry jello into Cool Whip in Cool Whip container.
Then fold into 1st mixture.

title: sensational spud soup
directions: Add soup, milk and seasonings to potatoes and water. Serve with bacon sprinkled on top.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in sealed jar.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Add melted butter to sugar.
Add eggs and mashed potatoes. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
I refrigerate these for several hours (even overnight).
Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut and deep fry.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, and oil until sugar is dissolved and pour over kraut mixture. Refrigerate. The longer it sets the better it tastes.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mixes into milk in medium saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Place plastic wrap on surface of filling.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with Cool Whip.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; add butter. Press into a 13 x 9 inch pan. Melt in microwave for 1-1/2 minutes;
marshmallows and orange juice. Add cream cheese and cool whip. Pour into crust.
You may top with cherries.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Place noodles in a pot of boiling salt water and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Prepare spinach from package.
Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add carrots and mushrooms.
Cook until crisp and tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and oregano. Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer in one-half each of noodles, cottage cheese, spinach, sauce mixture and 1/3 of the cheese slices.
Repeat.
Place remaining third of Monterey Jack on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine the boiling water and Jell-O.
When congealed, add the salad dressing immediately. Beat until double.
Blend into the Jell-O mixture the cottage cheese, onion, celery and salt and pepper.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cranberry nut salad
directions: Mix gelatins in large bowl; add hot water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: nut roll
directions: Cut shortening and flour as you do for pie dough.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs, sugar, salt and sour cream.
Mix and add with flour and shortening.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: no-rise yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar with melted butter in large bowl.
Add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture, then add flour and stir until mixed.
Bake by dropping spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
The batter does not need to rise to bake or to refrigerate.
Place in airtight bowl and keep refrigerated.
Will last several days.
Use as needed.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in heavy skillet; add rest of ingredients, except Rice Krispies and coconut.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add Rice Krispies; make into small balls and roll in coconut.
"A favorite holiday treat of ours!"

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate coon cheese.
Mix uncooked sausage, cheese and Bisquick well.
Add red pepper if you wish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour vanilla pudding powder over fruit. Let sit overnight. Add cut up bananas before serving.

title: bacon-pineapple appetizer
directions: Soak ingredients for 2 to 3 hours.
Wrap pineapple in 1/2 slice bacon.
Microwave 1 minute, turning as needed, until done. Use lean bacon for best results.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Stir to separate meat; add taco season.
Layer beans, peppers, chips and meat mix, ending with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fritter batter
directions: Beat eggs and milk in medium bowl until well blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oil and mix.
Cut up fruit or vegetables.
Add to or dip into batter.
Drop into hot deep fat (375°) and fry until brown.
Do not crowd.
Drain on paper towels.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in microwave on Full power for 20 to 22 minutes.
Stir once or twice during cooking.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form in large mixing bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at high speed.
Continue beating until mixture thickens and candy starts to lose its gloss.
Beating may require about 12 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen pieces.

title: layered sandwich
directions: Slice 3/4-inch layer off top (the lid) of bread.
Hollow out loaf, leaving 1/2-inch thick bread shell.
Brush inside of loaf and underside of lid with salad dressing.
Layer half the lettuce, meat, Mozzarella, meat, tomatoes, meat, Cheddar cheese and remaining lettuce.
Firmly pack down and replace the lid.
Cut sandwich in wedges to serve.
Wrap unsliced loaf well and refrigerate.
Try adding onions, mushrooms and peppers.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk until blended.
Stir in crabmeat, Swiss and onions.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In casserole bottom melt margarine.
Pour in some favorite stuffing mix.
Save some for top.
Add zucchini chunks and carrots. Mix sour cream, cream of celery soup and chopped onion.
Pour over zucchini and carrots.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buffet cheese-scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water for 10 minutes and drain. Cook onion in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: southern chili
directions: Saute chuck, sausage, onions, green pepper and garlic; drain. Add all other ingredients and cook at least 3 hours.
Never allow it to boil.
Serve with sour cream and Southern corn bread.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put Wesson oil and
crackers in Ziploc bag and shake to coat. Mix dressing with
dill
weed and add to bag.
Shake to coat. Pour out on
paper
towel
to
drain.
Store in plastic container.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cream the sugar and shortening together until creamy and light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla; sift together with baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Make a heavy smooth paste of the cocoa and boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add and blend well.
Pour into pans and bake for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: canned okra
directions: Put ingredients in a large pan and boil 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
For fried okra, rinse thoroughly.
Roll in meal and fry as you would any fried okra.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet with margarine. Let dough thaw and rise until double in size.
Roll dough out flat.
Beat eggs; add oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Spread 3/4 egg mixture all over flattened dough.
Top with shredded cheese and pepperoni slices.
Roll up like a jelly roll; seal edges and ends (be sure they are sealed).
Place on greased pan and spread rest of egg mixture over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.
While hot, brush with margarine on top and sides.
Serve hot.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel, core and slice apples and place in a baking dish.
Mix flour, oats and sugar.
Melt oleo and mix with dry.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: leah's pound cake
directions: Beat until creamy, oleo and sugar.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add salt, mace, lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Mix.
Pour in greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake two hours at 325°.

title: turkey carcass soup
directions: Combine the turkey carcass, water, poultry seasoning and thyme in large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.

title: glazed chicken and grapes
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Spray a cold, large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Heat skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken to skillet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once during cooking.
Transfer chicken to serving plates.
Cover to keep warm.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Melt
oleo
in
saucepan.
Add sugar and milk, stirring well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until it spins a
thread.
Remove
from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: oatmeal hurry-ups
directions: In a saucepan, combine cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and margarine; cook over low to moderate heat, stirring constantly, until margarine is melted and mixture comes to a boil.
Continue boiling two minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow cookies to set; store in covered container. Makes about 45 cookies, each with 93 calories, 4.25 g fat and .88 mg cholesterol.

title: maple hot chocolate
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in hot water and butter, bring to a boil.
Add the milk, maple flavoring, vanilla and 8 marshmallows.
Heat through, stirring occasionally, until marshmallows are melted.
Ladle into mugs and top each with a marshmallow.
Yields 4 servings.

title: brad's pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta and drain.
Add pepperoni, olives, green peppers and onion.
Add dressings and mix well.
Let chill for about one hour before serving.
I prefer to let set overnight.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and pineapple.
Fold in pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Chill overnight.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until clear.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat 20 to 30 minutes, until desired thickness. Keeps up to 1 month in refrigerator.

title: bagna cauda(garlic, oil and anchovy sauce)
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan and add the garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring, without browning.
Add the wine and cook until reduced by half.
Add the butter, a little at a time, beating rapidly with a wire whisk.
Stir in the anchovy, season with pepper and serve hot. Yield:
about 3/4 cup.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar and corn syrup in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter is dissolved.
Add corn flakes and peanuts.
Stir until well coated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 1 1/4 hours with 1-inch water, covering them. Cool; debone chicken.
Place chicken in large buttered casserole dish.
Mix 3 soups and pour over chicken.
Place finely chopped onion over this.
Add stuffing.
Slowly drip batter over this; add broth from chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
This is a meal in itself.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute bacon until crisp, drain well.
Saute garlic and onions until wilted and add tomatoes.
Stir and cook until liquid is reduced by 1/2, approximately 1 hour.
Pour into chafing dish, add bacon and cheese.
Serve when the cheese has melted.
Keep warm for dipping with Fritos or Doritos.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat together 6 cups water and 4 cups sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, remove and break up with fork until mixture is like mush.
Add 3 quarts ginger ale.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: townsend ice cream
directions: You will need a 1 gallon freezer.

title: old family recipe cake
directions: Slice angel food cake crossways into three parts.
Spread layers with apricot jam and stack.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip.
Garnish top of cake with peach slices.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: taco frijoles para los ninos(bean taco for the little ones)
directions: Place chips on bottom of individual serving bowls.
Place beans in individual bowls.
Top with lettuce, cheese and onion.
Sprinkle with salsa pequin, if desired.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; gently shape into 1-inch balls (a meatball scoop can be used).
Cook meatballs in shortening in 12-inch skillet until brown.
Remove meatballs from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.

title: crispy fried okra
directions: Wash okra and drain well.
Remove tip and stem.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add egg to okra and toss to coat.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dredge okra.
Deep fry in hot oil at 375° until golden brown.

title: deviled clam dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Add juice from minced clams until mixture is the right consistency.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil in a deep dish pie pan.
Work Crisco into the flour as if making biscuits.
Then work in the iced water, making a dough for dumplings and crust.
Flour the board and roll the dough out with rolling pin.
Roll thin, then cut in 1-inch strips all across the board.
Have the berries boiling and drop dumplings all across the pan, dipping the juice over the dumplings and making sure to cover good.
Then roll a top crust while berries are still boiling.
Place cover on pie.
Cover the top with butter and then sugar.
Place in oven and brown the top, being careful to not let burn.

title: chocolate delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until very light brown.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature; blend well.
Mix with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate until firm enough to mold into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix barbecue sauce and jelly; dissolve over medium heat.
Once sauce is dissolved, cut wieners into small pieces and add to the sauce. Cook slow until wieners are done. Serve with toothpicks.

title: pea soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cubed potatoes, peas and onions and Italian dressing.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in sour cream; blend well.
Serve warm, garnished with fresh mint.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add remaining ingredients. Beat until well blended.
Pour into a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: braised beef tips
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat on all sides. Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir gradually into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stollen
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast.
Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead in remaining 5 ingredients.
Set aside 1/3 of the dough.
Divide remaining dough in three equal parts and roll each in a strip about 12 inches long.
Braid.
Put on greased baking sheet.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all together
until blended; pour in greased baking dish. Crumble 1
sleeve
Ritz crackers for top.
Melt 1 stick butter and drizzle over mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut buttered bread into crouton size pieces.
Stir eggs and milk together in a large bowl.
Mix all the remaining ingredients in with milk and egg mixture.
Pour into a buttered (or spray with Pam) 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
